Arrays (but not lists) can be declared at the top level but they are immutable?
Pass by value makes this ok (copy to function is mutable)? (Nope: use "data")

Literals with missing elements (ie. less values specified then length, or
numeric indexes) are only valid where the subtype has a valid zero value that
can be used for the missing items (ie. numeric, or nullable reftype)

